payload.name: iTOW
payload.description: GPS time of week of the navigation epoch. See the section iTOW timestamps in Integration manual for details.

fields.name: gnssId
fields.description: GNSS identifier (see Satellite Numbering) for assignment

fields.name: svId
fields.description: Satellite identifier (see Satellite Numbering) for assignment

fields.name: elev
fields.description: Elevation (range: +/-90), unknown if out of range

fields.name: azim
fields.description: Azimuth (range 0-360), unknown if elevation is out of range

bit_fields.name: qualityInd
bit_fields.description: Signal quality indicator: 0 = no signal, 1 = searching signal, 2 = signal acquired, 3 = signal detected but unusable, 4 = code locked and time synchronized, 5, 6, 7 = code and carrier locked and time synchronized

bit_fields.name: svUsed
bit_fields.description: 1 = Signal in the subset specified in Signal Identifiers is currently being used for navigation

bit_fields.name: health
bit_fields.description: Signal health flag: 0 = unknown, 1 = healthy, 2 = unhealthy

bit_fields.name: diffCorr
bit_fields.description: 1 = differential correction data is available for this SV

bit_fields.name: smoothed
bit_fields.description: 1 = carrier smoothed pseudorange used

bit_fields.name: orbitSource
bit_fields.description: Orbit source: 0 = no orbit information is available for this SV, 1 = ephemeris is used, 2 = almanac is used, 3 = AssistNow Offline orbit is used, 4 = AssistNow Autonomous orbit is used, 5, 6, 7 = other orbit information is used

bit_fields.name: ephAvail
bit_fields.description: 1 = ephemeris is available for this SV

bit_fields.name: almAvail
bit_fields.description: 1 = almanac is available for this SV

bit_fields.name: anoAvail
bit_fields.description: 1 = AssistNow Offline data is available for this SV

bit_fields.name: aopAvail
bit_fields.description: 1 = AssistNow Autonomous data is available for this SV

bit_fields.name: sbasCorrUsed
bit_fields.description: 1 = SBAS corrections have been used for a signal in the subset specified in Signal Identifiers

bit_fields.name: rtcmCorrUsed
bit_fields.description: 1 = RTCM corrections have been used for a signal in the subset specified in Signal Identifiers

bit_fields.name: slasCorrUsed
bit_fields.description: 1 = QZSS SLAS corrections have been used for a signal in the subset specified in Signal Identifiers

bit_fields.name: prCorrUsed
bit_fields.description: 1 = Pseudorange corrections have been used for a signal in the subset specified in Signal Identifiers

bit_fields.name: crCorrUsed
bit_fields.description: 1 = Carrier range corrections have been used for a signal in the subset specified in Signal Identifiers

bit_fields.name: doCorrUsed
bit_fields.description: 1 = Range rate (Doppler) corrections have been used for a signal in the subset specified in Signal Identifiers
